		<profileDesc>
			<abstract>
				<p>I describe a querying criterion that attempts to minimize the error of a learner by minimizing its estimated squared bias. I describe experiments with locally-weighted regression on two simple problems , and observe that this &quot;bias-only&quot; approach outperforms the more common &quot;variance-only&quot; exploration approach, even in the presence of noise.</p>
